{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbb4119f9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1653"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1653"},"text":"§ 1653.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Compensation districts; judicial proceedings","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbb4119fa-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1653/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Secretary of Labor is authorized to extend compensation districts established under the Longshore and Harbor Workers’ Compensation Act, approved ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1927-03-04"},"text":"March 4, 1927","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/1424"},"text":"44 Stat. 1424","children":[],"tail":") ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s901"},"text":"33 U.S.C. 901","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], or to establish new compensation districts, to include any area to which this chapter applies; and to assign to each such district one or more deputy commissioners, as the Secretary may deem necessary."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbb4119fb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1653/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Judicial proceedings provided under sections 18 and 21 of the Longshore and Harbor Workers’ Compensation Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s918"},"text":"33 U.S.C. 918","children":[],"tail":", 921] in respect to a compensation order made pursuant to this chapter shall be instituted in the United States district court of the judicial district wherein is located the office of the deputy commissioner whose compensation order is involved if his office is located in a judicial district, and if not so located, such judicial proceedings shall be instituted in the judicial district nearest the base at which the injury or death occurs."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbb4119fc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1941-08-16/ch357/s3"},"text":"Aug. 16, 1941, ch. 357, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/55/623"},"text":"55 Stat. 623","children":[],"tail":"; 1946 Reorg. Plan No. 2, § 3, eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1946-07-16"},"text":"July 16, 1946","children":[],"tail":", 11 F.R. 7873, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/1095"},"text":"60 Stat. 1095","children":[],"tail":"; 1950 Reorg. Plan No. 19, § 1, eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1950","children":[],"tail":", 15 F.R. 3178, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1271"},"text":"64 Stat. 1271","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/426/s27/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–426, § 27(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-09-28"},"text":"Sept. 28, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1654"},"text":"98 Stat. 1654","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbb4119fd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbb4119fe-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbb4119ff-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Longshore and Harbor Workers’ Compensation Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1927-03-04/ch509"},"text":"act Mar. 4, 1927, ch. 509","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/1424"},"text":"44 Stat. 1424","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 18 (§ 901 et seq.) of Title 33, Navigation and Navigable Waters. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s901"},"text":"section 901 of Title 33","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbb411a00-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsecs. (a), (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/426"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–426","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Longshore and Harbor Workers’ Compensation Act” for “Longshoremen’s and Harbor Workers’ Compensation Act”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idbb411a01-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idbb411a02-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1984 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/426"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–426","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-09-28"},"text":"Sept. 28, 1984","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/426/s28/e/1"},"text":"section 28(e)(1) of Pub. L. 98–426","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s901"},"text":"section 901 of Title 33","children":[],"tail":", Navigation and Navigable Waters."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"idbb411a03-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"idbb411a04-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Secretary of Labor” and “Secretary” substituted for “Federal Security Administrator” and “Administrator”, respectively, in subsec. (a), pursuant to Reorg. Plan No. 19 of 1950, § 1, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1950-05-24"},"text":"May 24, 1950","children":[],"tail":", 15 F.R. 3178, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1271"},"text":"64 Stat. 1271","children":[],"tail":", which transferred functions of Federal Security Administrator to Secretary of Labor."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Previously, “Federal Security Administrator” and “Administrator” substituted for “United States Employees’ Compensation Commission” and “Commission” pursuant to Reorg. Plan No. 2 of 1946, § 3, eff. ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1946-07-16"},"text":"July 16, 1946","children":[],"tail":", 11 F.R. 7873, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/1095"},"text":"60 Stat. 1095","children":[],"tail":", which abolished United States Employees’ Compensation Commission and transferred its functions to Federal Security Administrator."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
